240763,-0.02189843,0.03877584,0.01725071,-0.01530515,0.06239174,-0.05971494,-0.00994724,0.02689668,-0.02249269,0.06899534,-0.01233379,-0.02638404,-0.07674344,0.00566417,0.02607013,-0.02082474,0.01214560,-0.05383554,0.00373011,0.01445794,0.02056028,0.03227758,-0.01049344,-0.06344822,-0.06197974,-0.02146898,0.03835265,-0.01737683,-0.03893610,-0.05939425,-0.01898707,0.05223594,-0.02702314,0.02254439,0.04465147,0.04278444,0.04387263,0.04826618,0.05910738,0.10776450,-0.01836677,0.00959460]',E'Queue Properties {#properties}\n\nQueues have properties that define how they behave. There is a set\nof mandatory properties and a map of optional ones:\n\n * Name\n * Durable (the queue will survive a broker restart)\n * Exclusive (used by only one connection and the queue will be deleted when that connection closes)\n * Auto-delete (queue that has had at least one consumer is deleted when last consumer unsubscribes)\n * Arguments (optional; used by plugins and broker-specific features such as message TTL, queue length limit, etc)','{"source": "rabbitmq", "version": "3.13", "language": "amqp", "title": "Queues", "section_title": "queues", "url": "https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-website/blob/main/docs/queues.md", "topics": "rabbitmq,messaging,queues", "categories": "messaging,queue,amqp"}');
