79,0.16116352,-0.08287998,0.06205745,0.00027529,0.00992441,0.08598689,0.00399941,0.04219649,0.00568144,-0.00941463,0.10572269,0.00531904,-0.00094701,-0.02150125,-0.01610582,-0.03505406,-0.01833620,0.03989742,-0.06258342,-0.02863267,0.01713787,0.04753204,0.05969850,-0.02655324,-0.02820353,-0.03269392,0.01668339,0.05912864,-0.06828944,0.02411094,-0.03238015,0.00919000,0.08547968,-0.02394805,0.04422666,0.00136306,0.00288571,0.06549561,0.03368031,0.03718030,0.09277001,-0.00610120,0.03856810]',E'Optional Arguments {#optional-arguments}\n\n:::\n\nFor example, [queue type](./quorum-queues) (`x-queue-type`) and max number\nof [queue priorities](./priority) (`x-max-priority`) must be set at queue declaration time\nand cannot be changed after that.\n\nOptional queue arguments can be set differently:\n\n * To groups of queues using [policies](./policies) (recommended)\n * On a per-queue basis when a queue is declared by a client\n * For the `x-queue-type` argument, [using a default queue type](./vhosts#default-queue-type)','{"source": "rabbitmq", "version": "3.13", "language": "amqp", "title": "Queues", "section_title": "queues", "url": "https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-website/blob/main/docs/queues.md", "topics": "rabbitmq,messaging,queues", "categories": "messaging,queue,amqp"}');
