4,0.00854149,-0.00425750,0.04801781,-0.03742186,0.06301112,-0.05668563,0.01697014,0.05606826,-0.00012028,0.03662097,-0.02224253,-0.01201072,-0.11447961,0.06968523,0.00650412,-0.00462763,-0.04934866,-0.04310737,-0.01042021,0.00055712,0.00431684,0.08321898,0.02380982,-0.03159377,-0.01923972,-0.04307847,-0.01628225,-0.00895444,-0.05180570,0.01792441,0.02056250,0.04766386,0.01706133,0.00688226,-0.01526920,-0.01439372,0.02112999,0.07801735,0.03309425,0.00117681,-0.02660723,0.00449362]',E'Exclusive (Client Connection-Specific) Queues {#exclusive-queues}\n\nAn attempt to use an exclusive queue from\na different connection will result in a channel-level exception\n<code>RESOURCE_LOCKED</code> with an error message that says\n<code>cannot obtain exclusive access to locked queue</code>.\n\nExclusive queues are deleted when their declaring connection is closed\nor gone (e.g. due to underlying TCP connection loss). They therefore\nare only suitable for client-specific transient state.\n\nIt is common to make exclusive queues server-named.','{"source": "rabbitmq", "version": "3.13", "language": "amqp", "title": "Queues", "section_title": "queues", "url": "https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-website/blob/main/docs/queues.md", "topics": "rabbitmq,messaging,queues", "categories": "messaging,queue,amqp"}');
