82,0.01762801,0.01874573,0.01889761,-0.03689349,0.05939671,-0.07190798,0.01394231,-0.02030284,-0.01304172,0.03795350,-0.05087846,0.04638970,-0.06272697,-0.00426171,-0.00670819,-0.00604427,-0.00481024,-0.06600827,0.00405905,0.00456375,-0.03129439,0.05755915,0.01700988,-0.00311351,-0.07944173,-0.04463106,0.03068165,-0.05131451,-0.03988462,-0.01672773,0.04397399,0.12496197,-0.03438652,0.04957344,-0.01988282,-0.02586799,-0.00402462,-0.00123865,0.04469553,0.02965945,0.02958421,0.01185889]',E'Avoid Temporary Queues with Well-Known Names {#shared-temporary-queues}\n\nA [temporary queue](#temporary-queues) that is not exclusive can be client named and shared\nbetween multiple consumers. This, however, is not recommended and can lead to a race condition\nbetween RabbitMQ node operations and client recovery.\n\nConsider the following scenario:\n\n * A consumer uses an auto-delete queue with a well-known names\n * Client''s connection fails\n * Client detects it and initiates connection recovery','{"source": "rabbitmq", "version": "3.13", "language": "amqp", "title": "Queues", "section_title": "queues", "url": "https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-website/blob/main/docs/queues.md", "topics": "rabbitmq,messaging,queues", "categories": "messaging,queue,amqp"}');
