-0.01299138,0.02075282,0.05930631,0.03378747,0.00256864,0.01150385,0.03623985,0.04471385,0.01286765,0.05801671,-0.00054876,0.01620787,-0.04907250,0.01469335,-0.01610795,-0.02443157,0.07289675,-0.08431837,0.06123628,-0.00963459,0.02292914,0.03858785,-0.04334415,-0.01185105,-0.00513672,-0.03550011,0.02086869,-0.04586931,-0.05089927,0.05793002,0.01486248,0.02900014,0.02483604,0.00011020,-0.00754313,-0.01597753,-0.00173343,0.03274453,0.08652423,0.04492617,-0.01503666,0.02827030]',E'Enabling Single Active Consumer on Quorum and Classic Queues\n\nSAC can be enabled when declaring a queue, with the\n`x-single-active-consumer` argument set to `true`.\n\n<Tabs groupId="amqp-version">\n<TabItem value="amqp-1.0" label="AMQP 1.0 (Java)" default>\n\nUsing the [RabbitMQ AMQP 1.0 Java client](https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-amqp-java-client):\n\n```java\nconnection.management().queue()\n    .name("my-queue")\n    .quorum()\n    .queue()\n    .singleActiveConsumer(true)\n    .declare();\n```\n\n</TabItem>\n<TabItem value="amqp-0-9-1" label="AMQP 0-9-1 (Java)">\n\n```java\nChannel ch = ...;\nMap<String, Object> arguments = new HashMap<String, Object>();\narguments.put("x-single-active-consumer", true);\nch.queueDeclare("my-queue", false, false, false, arguments);\n```\n\n</TabItem>\n</Tabs>','{"source": "rabbitmq", "version": "3.13", "language": "amqp", "title": "Consumers", "section_title": "consumers", "url": "https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-website/blob/main/docs/consumers.md", "topics": "rabbitmq,messaging,consumers", "categories": "messaging,queue,amqp"}');
