9,0.04830833,0.05602131,0.02719317,-0.04832649,0.06913278,-0.01371675,-0.04910940,-0.00037584,-0.04315451,0.11483322,-0.04895242,-0.00974986,-0.00819914,-0.02178313,0.00409212,-0.01384552,0.00882916,0.02939569,-0.00272556,-0.03239327,0.02700131,0.06036207,0.01137703,-0.00049225,-0.04659503,-0.01567132,0.02908600,-0.01798777,-0.03339455,-0.00296413,-0.02222120,0.00848564,-0.04462451,-0.00454574,-0.04958285,-0.04961344,0.05066082,0.02814324,0.07169139,0.00831403,0.04086230,0.00022976]',E'Binding Durability\n\nBindings inherit durability from their source and destination. As such, bindings can be\n\n * Fully durable: both their exchange and destination/queue/stream are durable\n * Semi-durable: in practice this means that their exchange is durable and their destination/queue/stream is transient\n * Fully transient: both their exchange and destination/queue/stream are transient\n\nSupport for semi-durable and fully transient bindings will be dropped in the future.','{"source": "rabbitmq", "version": "3.13", "language": "amqp", "title": "Exchanges", "section_title": "exchanges", "url": "https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-website/blob/main/docs/exchanges.md", "topics": "rabbitmq,messaging,exchanges", "categories": "messaging,queue,amqp"}');
