,0.02828467,-0.03139763,0.01363265,0.07149559,0.04766816,0.00463642,0.05651070,-0.02782167,-0.04518824,-0.00415508,-0.03315964,0.06553829,-0.03119517,0.01216639,-0.06669017,0.01975882,-0.04899389,-0.02302787,0.04973494,-0.00509936,-0.02091836,0.03653592,0.00042478,0.00799493,-0.05995224,0.05941748,0.02870315,-0.05569129,-0.12520057,0.03575265,0.03105468,-0.01356258,0.08267710,0.03163214,-0.02805343,-0.08694104,-0.04355859,0.02600273,-0.00634564,0.04261820,0.00809762,-0.00168285]',E'Authentication Failures {#peer-authentication-failures}\n\nWhen a recent Erlang/OTP version is used, authentication failures contain\nmore information and cookie mismatches can be identified better:\n\n```ini\n* connected to epmd (port 4369) on warp10\n* epmd reports node ''rabbit'' running on port 25672\n* TCP connection succeeded but Erlang distribution failed\n\n* Authentication failed (rejected by the remote node), please check the Erlang cookie\n```\n\nSee the [CLI Tools guide](./cli) for more information.','{"source": "rabbitmq", "version": "3.13", "language": "amqp", "title": "Clustering Guide", "section_title": "clustering", "url": "https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-website/blob/main/docs/clustering.md", "topics": "rabbitmq,messaging,clustering", "categories": "messaging,queue,amqp"}');
