466,-0.02447045,0.04260012,0.03419423,0.01441745,0.06594221,-0.02690540,0.02130690,-0.03956369,0.00145901,0.05331616,-0.01038677,0.01553580,-0.03314985,0.02696454,-0.05288871,-0.01261669,-0.04978477,-0.02031966,0.00950343,0.02528307,-0.00728905,0.05230828,-0.03765301,-0.01656502,-0.03459157,0.01394391,0.05807012,-0.08823038,-0.01141615,0.01126801,-0.05852465,0.03478312,0.02719328,-0.01186436,-0.00732191,-0.07617140,-0.00248885,0.03816425,-0.00853848,0.09205382,-0.02550697,0.02970420]',E'Queue and Stream Leader Replica Placement {#replica-placement}\n\n* `client-local`, the default, will always pick the node the client is connected to\n * `balanced`, which takes into account the number of queues/leaders already running\n   on each node in the cluster; when there are relatively few\n   queues in the cluster, it picks the node with the least number of them; when there\n   are many (more than 1000 by default), it just picks a random node (calculating the\n   exact number can be slow with many queues, and a random choice is generally just as good)','{"source": "rabbitmq", "version": "3.13", "language": "amqp", "title": "Clustering Guide", "section_title": "clustering", "url": "https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-website/blob/main/docs/clustering.md", "topics": "rabbitmq,messaging,clustering", "categories": "messaging,queue,amqp"}');
